p.font: Actions can be used together or individually. Thus, we offer the possibility to select actions to address the user context. After selecting, a custom action plan will be created. Finally, it's possible to print or download this plan.

div.font: These are the actions identified through semistructured interviews. They are following the 5W1H model. In this case, these are the suggested actions to help catalog users to identify Test Debts caused by Low Code Coverage.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 9px; white-space: nowrap; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 328px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

p.font: These are the subtypes of Test Debts. Each subtype is considered to be a cause of a Test Debt. In this catalog, we present a set of actions for each subtype. For example, after clicking on the "Identification" activity, you can choose which subtype you want to handle. Here, we choose "Low Code Coverage", which has two related actions.

p.font: These are technical debt management activities. By clicking on any of these activities, you will see subtypes of Test Debts and its related actions. In this image, the "Identification" activity was selected.
